ly is not what you want. The hook\n  implementation function signature should be\n  <strong>%function($entity_type_manager, $entity, $fields, $delta)</strong>,\n  and the desired value should be returned. If/when it exists, this form element\n  will be greyed out.</em>\n</p>\n<p>The variables available to your code include:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><code>$entity_type_manager</code>: The entity type manager.</li>\n  <li><code>$entity</code>: The entity the field belongs to.</li>\n  <li><code>$fields</code>: The list of fields available in this entity.</li>\n  <li><code>$delta</code>: Current index of the field in case of multi-value computed fields (counting from 0).</li>\n  <li><code>$value</code>: The resulting value to be set above, or returned in your hook implementation).</li>\n</ul>\n      ','','8.3.5'),(5485,'\n<p>\n  Here\'s a simple example using the <code>$entity</code>-array which sets the computed field\'s value to the concatenation of fields (<code>field_a</code> and <code>field_b</code>) in an entity:\n  <ul>\n    <li><code>$value = $entity->field_a->value . $entity->field_b->value;</code></li>\n  </ul>\n</p>\n<p>\n  An alternative example using the <code>$fields</code>-array:\n  <ul>\n    <li><code>$value = $fields[\'field_a\'][0][\'value\'] . $fields[\'field_b\'][0][\'value\'];</code></li>\n  </ul>\n</p>\n    ','','8.3.5'),(5486,'The value will be truncated to @max_length characters.','','8.3.5'),(5487,'Code (PHP) to compute the <em>text</em> value','','8.3.5'),(5488,'The listed configuration will be updated.','','8.3.5'),(5489,'Are you sure you want to delete the @entity-type %label?','','8.3.5'),(5490,'Order','Sort order','8.3.5'),(5491,'Code (PHP) to compute the <em>long text</em> value','','8.3.5'),(5492,'For more information see W3C\'s <a href=\":html-specifications\">HTML Specifications</a> or use your favorite search engine to find other sites that explain HTML.','','8.3.5'),(5493,'If you do encounter problems, try using HTML character entities. A common example looks like &amp;amp; for an ampersand &amp; character. For a full list of entities see HTML\'s <a href=\":html-entities\">entities</a> page. Some of the available characters include:','','8.3.5'),(5494,'\n        <p>You can align images, videos, blockquotes and so on to the left, right or center. Examples:</p>\n        <ul>\n          <li>Align an image to the left: <code>&lt;img src=\"\" data-align=\"left\" /&gt;</code></li>\n          <li>Align an image to the center: <code>&lt;img src=\"\" data-align=\"center\" /&gt;</code></li>\n          <li>Align an image to the right: <code>&lt;img src=\"\" data-align=\"right\" /&gt;</code></li>\n          <li> and you can apply this to other elements as well: <code>&lt;video src=\"\" data-align=\"center\" /&gt;</code></li>\n        </ul>','','8.3.5'),(5495,'\n        <p>You can caption images, videos, blockquotes, and so on. Examples:</p>\n        <ul>\n            <li><code>&lt;img src=\"\" data-caption=\"This is a caption\" /&gt;</code></li>\n            <li><code>&lt;video src=\"\" data-caption=\"The Drupal Dance\" /&gt;</code></li>\n            <li><code>&lt;blockquote data-caption=\"Dries Buytaert\"&gt;Drupal is awesome!&lt;/blockquote&gt;</code></li>\n            <li><code>&lt;code data-caption=\"Hello world in JavaScript.\"&gt;alert(\"Hello world!\");&lt;/code&gt;</code></li>\n        </ul>','','8.3.5'),(5496,'Only images hosted on this site may be used in &lt;img&gt; tags.','','8.3.5'),(5497,'Lines and paragraphs are automatically recognized. The &lt;br /&gt; line break, &lt;p&gt; paragraph and &lt;/p&gt; close paragraph tags are inserted automatically. If paragraphs are not recognized simply add a couple of blank lines.','','8.3.5'),(5498,'Computed PHP (free input)','','8.3.5'),(5499,'Cache: default','','8.3.5'),(5500,'Sanitized','','8.3.5'),(5501,'Here you can change the caching of the formatted value: \"default\" means until it is saved again, \"off\" no caching, others are units to cache the value acco